This paper is primarily focused on action recognition in videos, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also proposes a new method for feature extraction using 3D convolutional neural networks, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of residual frames, which is a technique commonly used in video compression (cs.MM). The paper also involves the use of appearance features, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for improving performance, which could fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) category.
